      "id": "apt-351",
      "question": "A train of length 100 meters crosses a utility pole in how many seconds if its constant speed is 36 km/hr?",
      "category": "Quantitative",
      "subcategory": "Time & Speed",
      "options": [
        "10 seconds",
        "12.5 seconds",
        "8.2 seconds",
        "15 seconds"
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "A",
      "explanation": "To calculate the crossing time, we convert the speed from km/hr to m/s:\nSpeed in m/s = Speed in km/hr * (5 / 18)\nSpeed = 36 * (5 / 18) = 10 m/s.\nTime taken = Train Length / Speed\nTime = 100 / 10 = 10 seconds.",
      "difficulty": "Hard"
